Uses of Package
com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap

  • Packages that use com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap 
    Package Description
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap
    This package defines the API and base classes for the objects that are used to import or export LDAP directory entries to or from DSML and LDIF file formats.
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.apache
    The abstract base classes and concrete implementations for the Mojos that implement the goals of the plugin are defined in this package.
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.dsml  
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.ldif  
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.mojo

    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.opendj
    The abstract base classes and concrete implementations for the Mojos that implement the goals of the plugin are defined in this package.
    com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap.unboundid
    The abstract base classes and concrete implementations for the Mojos that implement the goals of the plugin are defined in this package.
  • Classes in com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap used by com.btmatthews.maven.plugins.ldap 
    Class and Description
    FormatHandler
    The interface that is implemented by objects that handle the DSML and LDIF file formats.
    FormatLogger
    The API used by FormatHandler, FormatReader and FormatWriter implementations to log information and error messages.
    FormatReader
    Implemented by objects that read change records from DSML or LDIF files.
    FormatWriter
    Implemented by objects that write directory entries to DSML or LDIF files.
    LDAPServer
    The interface that must be implemented by LDAP servers.
